Benepeteia /.bĕn″ə.pɪˈtaɪ.ə/ 

Based on the Greek word "Peripeteia", defined as "a sudden change of events or reversal of circumstances, 
especially in a literary work"¹, benepetia is an abrupt change in fortune producing favorable results (and coined by me).

1)  The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition
